## AI behaviour Rules

- Generate clean and beginner-friendly code
- Prefer readability over overly clever solutions
- Avoid unnecessary complexity
- Follow existing project structure and pattern
- Reuse existing components and styles whenever possible
- Do not create duplicate functionality
- Keep function small and modular
- Avoid overengineering simple features
- focus onn maintainable and production-friendly code


## Workflow Control Rules 
- Before making major changes, explain the implementation plan first
- if clarifying questions if requirements are unclear
- Do not assume missing requirements
- break complex tasks into smaller reviewable steps

## Safe Editing Rules 
- Do not modify multiple unrelated files without approval
- Minimized unexpected changes
- Avoid unncessary refactoring

## Review-First Behaviour
- Show planned changes before applying major edits
- Prefer review based workflow over autonomus execution
- Ask for confirmatio before:
     - deleting files
     - renaming files
     - restructuring folders
     - installing dependencies
     - modifying configurations

## Communication style
- Ask concise and relevant questions
- Clearly explain trade-off when multiple approaches available

## Agent Boundaries
- Never make irreversible changes without approval
- Never overcomplete simple solutions
- Prefer iterative development over one shot generation 

## Response Style
- Be concise and practical
- Avoid unnecessary explaination inside generated code